page.title: 05Axe and Compasses, East End
page.content: {The Axe and Compasses }was built four hundred years ago at East End.One hundred years ago an extension was built to be used as a dance hall.It was first called the Adds and Compass.There is an oak beam which is older than the pub which was first used on a ship or a barn.The doors, stairs and fire place are solid oak.There are pictures called "The Tipplers" and "The Rent Day" dated 1877 on the walls.A brick wall outside was built by French prisoners of War.Famous people to visit the pub are: Sir Alec Guinness (actor),Mick Jagger (singer) and Tom Baker (actor).
